This Snapshot Rolling Release Will Have A New Feature
1 Added Flatpak Backends On KDE Plasma Run sudo apt install plasma-discover-backend-flatpak
  If You Havent Install Flatpak sudo apt install flatpak
  If You Are using GNOME
  sudo apt install gnome-software-plugin-flatpak
  Add the Flathub repository
  flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://dl.flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo
  Reboot
2 Added Welcome Center Install It Using sudo apt install plasma-welcome
3 Added Copilot Install It Using sudo snap install copilot-desktop
4 Removed VERSION_ID=""
  VERSION=""
  VERSION_CODENAME=""
  And Added BUILD_ID=rolling
  Example
  PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
  NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
  ID=triaxis
  ID_LIKE=debian
  BUILD_ID=rolling
  How To Do It
  1 Open sudo nano /etc/os-release
  2 Remove
    VERSION_ID=""
    VERSION=""
    VERSION_CODENAME=""
  3 Add BUILD_ID=rolling After The ID_LIKE=debian
    Example
    PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
    NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
    ID=triaxis
    ID_LIKE=debian
    BUILD_ID=rolling
    Remove UBUNTU_CODENAME Because Its A Rolling Release Distro
  4 Ctrl X Y Enter
  5 sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
5 Added A Artwork Theme Its Called Slasher You Can Setup Here https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux/blob/main/How%20To%20Setup%20Triaxis%20Artwork%20Theme
